	<div id="id1ab5" class="post">
		<h2 class="title"><span class="image-wrapper"><img height="45" alt="Watch out Slate, it’s the Apple iTV" width="461" class="title" src="../../../resources/net.databinder.components.RenderedLabel/194feecc"/><span class="title">Watch out Slate, it’s the Apple iTV</span></span></h2>
		<div class="byline"><span>
			<span>By <span class="alias">Doctor Barnett</span>, <span>on September 12, 2006</span></span>
			<span id="id1ab6" class="tags">
					{&nbsp;<span><a href="../../../city/tag/apple/#selected-tag"><span>apple</span></a><span id="id1ab7">, </span></span><span><a href="../../../city/tag/tv/#selected-tag"><span>tv</span></a><span id="id1ab8">, </span></span><span><a href="../../../city/tag/slate/#selected-tag"><span>slate</span></a><span id="id1ab9">, </span></span><span><a href="../../../city/tag/boutin/#selected-tag"><span>boutin</span></a></span>&nbsp;}
			</span>
		</span></div>
		<div><p>Just when you thought Paul Boutin&#8217;s <em>Slate</em> piece about your lack of an &#8220;Apple iTV&#8221; <a href="http://technically.us/doc/articles/2006/08/09/slate-predicts-the-present-and-is-way-off">couldn&#8217;t be more wrong</a>, Apple actually does <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2006/09/12/live-from-the-steve-jobs-keynote-its-showtime/">announce a product</a> tentatively called the iTV (to mock P.B. ?).</p>


	<p><img src="/pictures/itv.jpg" alt="" /></p>


	<p>From Bousse-tin&#8217;s piece:</p>


	<blockquote>
		<p>&#8230;homes are consolidating around a two-hub model. <span class="caps">A PC</span> (or Mac) with some multimedia features anchors the home office, while a TV with some computerized gear—think TiVo, not desktop computer—owns the living room.</p>
	</blockquote>


	<p>No Paul, think &#8220;iTV.&#8221; Think that maybe the first company to make a good portable, synchronized <span class="caps">MP3</span> player could handle the pesky TV-integration problem.</p>


	<p>Or don&#8217;t think&#8212;keep gettin&#8217; the dirt from your &#8220;tech-savvy friends,&#8221; and writing about it in <em>Slate</em>&#8217;s tech-unsavvy column.</p></div>
	</div>
</div>

